  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>Alex and Bob have 30 matches. They play a game where on each turn a player can pick up between 1 and 6 matches. The player who picks up the last match wins. How many matches should Alex pick up at the beginning to guarantee that he wins?</denoised_question>",
  "solution_steps": "Step 1: In games where each player can remove 1 to 6 matches, the winning strategy is to leave a number of matches that is a multiple of 7 (since 6 + 1 = 7) for your opponent. Step 2: With 30 matches initially, the largest multiple of 7 less than or equal to 30 is 28. Step 3: To force the opponent into a losing position, Alex should remove 30 - 28 = 2 matches on his first turn. Step 4: By taking 2 matches, Alex leaves 28 matches. After every move Bob makes, Alex can always remove enough matches so that the total matches removed in both turns equals 7, keeping the remaining matches as a multiple of 7 until he wins.",
  "final_answer": "<answer>2</answer>"
}

